TITLE: Senate passes bipartisan bill to override Biden's handout to Chinese solar companies
SUMMARY: The Senate passed a resolution Wednesday evening to strike down President Biden's actions last year which allow Chinese solar panel manufacturers to skirt tariffs.

TITLE: Jets' Sauce Gardner says Aaron Rodgers couldn't believe he didn't know A-list actress at Knicks-Heat game
SUMMARY: Jets cornerback Sauce Gardner revealed Aaron Rodgers couldn't believe Gardner didn't recognize a famous actress sitting near them at the Knicks-Heat game Tuesday night.

TITLE: Giants pitcher Logan Webb says most of the team 'has the s--ts' after Mexico City series
SUMMARY: The San Francisco Giants recently finished a two-game set in Mexico City, but apparently the food south of the border has upset the stomachs of most of the team.

TITLE: WWE star Sonya Deville's stalker agrees to plea deal after attempted kidnapping
SUMMARY: Sonya Deville's stalker Phillip Thomas has been sentenced to 15 years in prison after striking a plea deal following an attempted kidnapping of the WWE star in August 2020.

TITLE: New Mexico delegates renew push for broader protection at Chaco National Park
SUMMARY: New Mexico delegates renewed a push for broader protection for the Chaco Culture National Historical Park. The legislation will provide a 10-mile buffer around the national park.

TITLE: Washington police fatally shoot man armed with shotgun in his yard
SUMMARY: Washington police officers fatally shot a man who was armed with a shotgun in his front yard. Police responded to a 911 call saying the man was suffering from mental health issues.

TITLE: Michigan passes bill to protect abortion-seekers from discrimination
SUMMARY: The Michigan Legislature has passed a bill that would prohibit employers from discriminating or retaliating against female employees for receiving abortions.

TITLE: California sees more snow fall halfway through spring
SUMMARY: California is still seeing snow fall halfway through spring. The unusual winter weather is being caused by an unseasonably cold system spinning off San Francisco Bay.

TITLE: State Department 'unable to confirm' video purporting to show drone attack on Kremlin
SUMMARY: The State Department says it's "unable to confirm" the authenticity of a video supposedly showing a drone attack on the Kremlin.

TITLE: Patrick Mahomes, Stephen Curry set to return for The Match alongside teammates Travis Kelce, Klay Thompson
SUMMARY: The Kansas City Chiefs will face the Golden State Warriors June 29. Patrick Mahomes and Travis Kelce will face Stephen Curry and Klay Thompson in The Match at Wynn Golf Club.

TITLE: WWE lands Olympic gold medalist Tamyra Mensah-Stock
SUMMARY: Tamyra Mensah-Stock has made a major career decision, signing with the WWE. After winning an Olympic medal in Tokyo, Mensah-Stock hinted that she could join the WWE.

TITLE: Curvy mermaid statue in Italy makes a viral splash as residents debate if it's 'vulgar' or 'beautiful'
SUMMARY: A cheeky and buxom mermaid statue created to honor an Italian Nobel Prize winner has appeared to confuse residents of a small port city and the rest of the world.

TITLE: Kansas City becomes latest Dem-run city to form reparations commission, seek payments for Black residents
SUMMARY: Kansas City's reparations commission is up and running with the appointment of 13 members who will be seeking taxpayer dollars for payments to eligible Black residents in the area.

TITLE: Tennessee football player sings national anthem ahead of Vols' baseball game
SUMMARY: Before winning their eighth-straight game, the 18th-ranked Tennessee Vols had a member of the football team sing the national anthem before a baseball game.

TITLE: Critics explode over US Navy's use of drag queen to solve recruiting crisis: 'What NOT to do'
SUMMARY: Critics exploded on the U.S. Navy over its decision to use a drag queen sailor to help persuade new recruits amid the military's massive recruitment crisis.

TITLE: Massachusetts man awarded $13M after serving 32 years for wrongful arson conviction
SUMMARY: Victor Rosario, 35, has been awarded $13 million from the city of Lowell, Massachusetts, after spending 32 years in prison for an arson he did not commit.

TITLE: Georgia Gov. Kemp signs bill to ban outside election funds
SUMMARY: Georgia Gov. Kemp signed a bill that would ban funding for elections from outside groups. The state will still allow contributions to the federal or state government.

TITLE: California leads blue state charge against Florida restrictions on transition surgeries
SUMMARY: California Attorney General Rob Bonta is leading a charge of Democratic-led states against Florida's new rule banning Medicaid dollars from being used for transition surgeries.

TITLE: California construction site collapses, trapping workers
SUMMARY: California emergency workers rescued six construction workers in Glendale after a building collapse on Wednesday. Some workers were stuck at least 30 feet in the air on cranes.

TITLE: Politifact defends Randi Weingarten: ‘Misleading’ to claim she opposed reopening schools
SUMMARY: Politifact published an analysis that insisted there needs to be additional context to the claim that Randi Weingarten opposed opening reopening schools during the pandemic.

TITLE: Georgia couple awarded $135.5M for damages from polluted land, water
SUMMARY: A Georgia couple has been awarded $135.5M for damages from polluted land and water. The lawsuit says Silicon Ranch Corp. developed over 160 solar panel facilities across the U.S.

TITLE: Billionaire Dem mega-donor bankrolling Trump accuser's rape lawsuit visited Epstein's private island
SUMMARY: A billionaire Democratic mega-donor who's currently bankrolling a rape lawsuit against former President Donald Trump visited the private island of sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

TITLE: Toronto-area man jailed for counseling suicide, causing 2 deaths
SUMMARY: Kenneth Law, 57, of Mississauga, Ontario has been arrested for allegedly providing lethal substances to two people at risk of suicide.

TITLE: NJ Republicans eye wind turbine construction moratorium over whale death concerns
SUMMARY: New Jersey Republicans and other opponents of shoreside wind turbines have proposed a moratorium of up to 60 days on construction to assess potential effects on whale mortality.

TITLE: Texas teacher arrested over improper relationship with student: police
SUMMARY: Newman International Academy teacher Alberto De La Cruz was arrested and charged with an improper relationship between educator and student. He was a high school athletic director.
